HEADWORD: Sickish
<hw>Sick"ish</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Somewhat sick or
diseased.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Somewhat sickening; <as>as, a <ex>sickish</ex>
taste</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Sick"ish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Sick"ish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sickle</ent>⟦br⟧
